main event: A military observation reported a single unidentified object in the Pacific Ocean on November 29, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed visually but lacked sufficient data for evaluation., The report considered it a possible aircraft sighting., Echo I and II satellites were confirmed to not be in the area., Other explanations, such as additional satellites, were ruled out., The duration of the observation was not reported.
sighted object: one bright object in the air
